items.description:
用于辅助批量操作txt文件的一个winfrom工具，自己编的，所以有啥需求评论说下，没事时候会更新下，图像处理就别说了，我也不会。

使用前建议先用自带的自动图像识别打标工具处理下，在文件夹里生成同名txt

如果你没用其他工具自动标注tag，会提示黄框，点击上面那个黄框的按钮就是自动生成同名的txt文件。

最主要还是用右上角绿色框的批量操作部分功能，使用前需要左边框中选取图片，可以使用ctrl和shfit辅助选取，然后点击批量操作就会对选取图片的txt文件进行操作。

也就大概测试了下，有啥bug评论区说下。

重申一下，这个不是自动识别图片自动标注tag的，

只是为了方便因为自动识别不足，而补充的批量向txt文件里增加删除修改操作的小工具，不能识别图片。

v1.1版本 ：修复了一些bug，批量时候不会重复报提示信息了，外加增加了一个统计功能

items.name: The Conspiracy - LoRA (Delta Green Style)
items.description:
You are cordially invited to a night at the opera.

The conspiracy began in 1927, following the raid on Innsmouth and the confirmation of what was previously local legends. The conspiracy would go by many names in the years hence, but has always been referred to internally by its security clearance its members claim: DELTA GREEN. Delta Green would be shuttered and revived throughout the decades, embroiled in conflict with both domestic rivals and cosmic threats, but the mission remains. To gather intelligence on and suppress unnatural incursions, and to protect the public from the corrosive knowledge of such unnatural forces. It is a cruel profession, but we live in a cruel and inhuman universe.

Scientia est mors. To know is to die.

Update 23/6/3:

Minor update optimizing the model size from 144 MB to 19 MB. Shouldn't change the behavior in any meaningful way, but it should take up a bit less space on your hard drive.

Update 23/5/29:


I fixed a lot of issues with the LORA for beta2. While the filesize went up, it retains the style across a wider variety of models and is overall more responsive and flexible. This is especially true for the noise offset, and you should be able to make both very bright and very dark images. I still need to do some more testing and dataset refinement before I publish the "final" version. Important note: make sure to use "disfigured" or "bloody face" in the negative prompt, as these elements can emerge unprompted due to the nature of the dataset. It is something that I will work on to alleviate for the final version. I still recommend 0.7-1.0 for weights, but the model can be touchy when it comes to lighting at higher weights.

Original Post
Hey folks,

This is a follow-up to my old TI version of the Denis Detweiler "Delta Green" style (The Conspiracy - TI). It is based on the art for the Delta Green tabletop role-playing franchise, which transposes the Cthulhu mythos to a modern day conspiracy thriller setting. I was happy with the TI, but it didn't really work outside of SD 1.5, so I trained a larger data set (with aspect ratio bucketing). The LORA works better with more models, although I find that strongly "aesthetic" models tend to wash out the oil painting style that Detweiler's artwork is known for. I recommend using it with either more neutral models that were directly trained on 1.5 (like Vodka) or models with a more painterly baseline style (like Dreamshaper or A-Zorya RPG Artist Tools). The LORA has not been tested with any CLIP SKIP 2 models, so no guarantees that it works with those.

23/5/28 EDIT: I did some more testing, and found that Realistic Vision 2.0 is actually much better at retaining the original style than the more painterly models, so you might have good results with applying photoreal-aimed models and merges as well.

I've also found this negative TI to be helpful (Negative Embedding for Deliberate) for the RPG Artist Tools model, and I've used Lykon's personal negative embedding (Fast Negative Embedding) for Dreamshaper.


This initial release is an open alpha release. For weights, I recommend 0.7-1.0, although I'm still testing to find the best prompts. You can use the ddstyle tag, but it doesn't seem necessary and doesn't have much impact. This is my first LORA, and I think that I can improve the dataset quality & hyperparameters. I also want to try training the LORA on other models to see if it can better transfer the style while gaining the improved composition quality of those mixes. Also, right now the model is just trained on the style, and I can work on improving tagging/captioning for better subject knowledge as well.

If you've read this far down, I appreciate it, and I've to hear your feedback.

Thanks,
Machinique

modelVersions.name: beta3
modelVersions.description: Minor update. This is just a resize/optimization of beta2 while keeping a rank of 128 DIM. Shouldn't be any real change from beta3, but it will save on space. Thus, the sample prompts from beta2 will still work (with minor variations).

modelVersions.name: beta2
modelVersions.description:
I went through some more training iterations and fixed some major captioning issues. The dataset was expanded from 88 to 117 images as well. The trigger word does seem to be impactful now.

As a warning, facial disfigurement is prominent in the dataset and can come up unprompted. I'll work on revising the tagging in the future, but adding "bloody face" or "disfigured" to the negative prompt should help ward that off.

I will also note that while this version does much better at retaining the Delta Green style, and has better and more flexible offset noise, there are certain cases where alpha1 may be the better model, so feel free to use either.

modelVersions.name: alpha1
modelVersions.description: Trained on 88 images with first pass captioning by BLIP and then second pass edits. Aspect ratio bucketing was used with ratios of 768 x 512, 640 x 640, and 512 x 768

items.name: GDM STYLE Textual Inversion Luxury Modern Interior Design
items.description:
This is the ultimate TEXTUAL INVERSION for Luxury Modern Interior Design trained on the style of GDM with 26500 steps, 260 images. This Textual Inversion designed to be flexible and mixed into prompts instead of having a dedicated checkpoint.

RECOMMENDED SETTINGS SD 1.5:

Steps: 20

CFG: 16

Trigger Word: gdminteriorti

Prompt Example: gdminteriorti luxury modern interior design

Add a living room, dining, bath, bed etc.

Tip#1: Try to use the above Steps and CFG settings first and tweak from there. I think 20 steps may be the best and sometimes 50 steps can also be good. CFG 16 is best with least artifacts and after 20, will be a hit or a miss. But you can try other settings to fit your needs.

Tip#2: Using prompt "gdminteriorti luxury modern interior design" works best to trigger the look, then add your own prompt to spice up the picture! Or if you want to just try the raw mode, use only the trigger word gdminteriorti.

As a favor, please let me know your thoughts, feedback and give a review rating. I would truly appreciate it!

items.name: Muses - Erato
items.description:
Erato

The muse of lyric erotic poetry

Use for making nude men with the correct privates, works most of the time. It is a versatile model and can do a variety of styles. It can produce SFW and NSFW images. It can make male private parts without the need of LoRA. Although men was the focus, the model is very versatile, and can yield great results with the right prompt. All images in the showcase are straight prompt generations without inpainting, some were upsized in img2img. It has some RPG knowledge and can produce from close to photoreal to something that approaches anime if prompted correctly.

V3

The previous version was not converting to Diffusers so I felt an obligation to fix it. Instead I had to remake it. As before this model produces body variety and ages, unlike Euterpe that produces muscle guys with huge privates.

  • You do not need heavy prompting to get decent results, for best results:

  • Use Sampling steps between 25 and 40

  • Use CFG between 6.5 and 9

  • Sampling method DPM++ 2M Karras works well, Euler works as well, but leads to blurry results when upsizing. Feel free to experiment

  • You may not need many negatives, the folowing are recommended:

    • JuggernautNegative-neg

    • BadDream

    • UnrealisticDream

    • ng_deepnegative_v1_75t

    • verybadimagenegative_v1.3

  • If prompting a nude male you will most likely get something close to proper privates anatomy without using the word "penis", If it's close enough, go to img2img and you will most likely get something realistic. Not using penis should allow you keep women from having one as well.

  • If prompting "penis" you will definitely get one, larger and sometimes unrealistic, so use with care.

V2

The model was fully re-build from scratch. It now produces better body variety even when using generic negatives. It is versatile and can be used for more than photography. Be warned that it will not produce female private parts appropriately, and you will most likely end up with a futanari if you don't use negatives to take the private parts off.

NOTE: Version 2 does not convert to Diffusers and I am unable to repair the checkpoint. Feel free to use it in Automatic1111 and ComfyUI, but it will not work in InvokeAI. If you merge V2 with another checkpoint, the same thing will happen with the result. I do not want to take it down because it produces some nice outputs.

My other mixes:

Terpsicore: Muse of dance and mother to the sirens

This model used to reside here, not it has its own listing. Click the name of the muse to see that version. Use it to make Furry characters and hairier men.

Euterpe: The muse of flutes and music

Euterpe is a male focused nsfw model, it will generate private parts or similar even when not prompted and tends to avoid clothing. Good for fit men and possibly futa.

If you would like to get realistic sized male private parts, do not mention them explicitly and you will often get something close, upsize in img2img to improve them. If you would like something larger or well defined from the get go, then mention it explicitly.

items.name: Anatomic Tech - World Morph
items.description:
Anatomic Tech - World Morph 🫀

"the earth is a living organism, and we live by harnessing what constitute its anatomy"

This LoRA is trained to exploring the idea in the LITERAL sense !

so prepare yourself to see to meat ! A LOT of it !

Things To know:

  • you must use the trigger word AnatomicTechto activate it , and its fully functional! but here are things I discovered to make things more interesting !

  • you can add any body part/organ you know to decorate your prompt, but I always tend to pair it with blood vessels it generates amazing branching patterns .

  • for urban and architectural image you can spice things up with scifi, utopia

  • things are getting too soft and droopy ? add bones to organize things up!

  • you made a mess all over the place ? well add messy to the Negative prompt

  • use any anatomy related terms or mix with other world LoRAs, there are so many possibilities!

  • If you're prompting a character make you need to specify their clothing, or the LoRA with try to strip away their skin !!

Usage Tips :

  • healthy LoRA weight range from 0.8 to 1.3

  • send to img2img to flesh out more details or to strengthen the LoRA even more

  • I recommend checkpoints that works great with generating small details like "revAnimated",

  • use ConsoleNet Tiles to generate super resolutions and explore finer details

You can track my upcoming LoRAs on my 📌Ideas Pinboard

Happy exploration and consider rating ⭐

items.name: Landsknecht Outfit
items.description:
The Landsknechte (singular: Landsknecht, pronounced [ˈlantsknɛçt]), also rendered as Landsknechts or Lansquenets, were Germanic mercenaries used in pike and shot formations during the early modern period.

How to use

  • Optimal weight: 1 for strong "automatic" styling (less control) <lora:landknt:1>

    • 0.5 to 1: easier customization, but checkpoint can take over

  • Mandatory word: landknt

  • Optional words: with a hat, with armor, beard, mustache, long hair

  • Optimal settings : CFG 7/Hires fix 200%/DPM++ 2M Karras/20 steps

  • Compatible any checkpoint

  • Please take inspiration from the showcase prompts in case of doubt

Training data

  • Steps: 900

  • Images: 40 photographs with upscaling, sharpening, recoloring

  • Captioning: BLIP + manual review

  • Model: SD 1.5

  • Clip 1

  • 128/64
